research and development expenses increased $1.0 billion or 9%, primarily due to linkedin expenses and increased investments in cloud engineering, offset in part by a reduction in phone expenses. expenses included $745 million related to our acquisition of linkedin.
fiscal year 2016 compared with fiscal year 2015
research and development expenses decreased $58 million, primarily due to a reduction in phone expenses, driven by the change in strategy for the phone business, offset in part by increased strategic investments and acquisitions to drive cloud innovation.
